Intended usage: COMMON

SCP files are usually created by disk preservation tools like the software that is used to drive the "SuperCard Pro" hardware. The SCP files contain the low-level flux data of the disk and thus can be used to fully preserve the contents of a floppy disk. These files then can be used to create a copy of the original disk, or they can be used in emulators for providing the floppy disk contents to the emulated system.

